This paper deals with parameter reduction in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on hashing-based compression methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization landscapes and back-propagation, which are relevant to neural network theory (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper provides empirical verifications, which suggests that it could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
